nd communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":58,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":69,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":71,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Byndlose was born in 1500, in Westmorland, England, his father, Sir William Byndlose, was 25 and his mother, Lady Cecilie Thomas, was 24. He married Eleanor Berners Palmer in 1518, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 19 November 1584, in Borwick, Lancashire, England, at the age of 84."},"et":{"1500–19 November 1584":"1500–19. november 1584","1500–1584":"1500–1584","1504–1589":"1504–1589","1530–1595":"1530–1595","1540–1631":"1540–1631","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1476–Female":"1476–Surnud","1571":"1571","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","19 November 1584":"19. november 1584","1589":"1589","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1631":"1631","1476":"1476","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","1540":"1540","1595":"1595","1584":"1584","1518":"1518","about 1540":"umbes 1540","1549":"1549","1504":"1504","Westmoreland, England":"Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Halyston, W